content.description: Up in smoke is just down the trail from Hot Chicks. An obvious belay area is below the climb right before you head downhill to Cockblocker. 5 bolts. Maybe 60 ft or so.
content.location: In between hot chicks and cockblocker.

content.description: Starts just to the right of "Hot Chicks on Wet Bikes"
content.location: Starts just to the right of "Hot Chicks on Wet Bikes"

content.description: A moderate start on obvious features veers left to s slabby and reachy crux.  Clip the bolt and pull over the small roof on great jugs to a finish out of sight.
content.location: Starts to the right of a dihedral and looks deceptively moderate from below.

content.description: A long moderate slab gets gradually steeper until it gets vertical with a small roof near the end.  A 60m rope may not reach the bottom to clean.
content.location: Just left of Cockblocker at the bottom of the long, sloping ramp.  The trail disappears into a thicket just past here and soon dwindles into nothing.

content.description: Sweet climb up an arete with a strange finish.  Powerful and difficult climbing to the first clip with uneven landing area. Balancy and fun.
content.location:
First bolted route that you get to as you hike down route to crag.  If you get to the strange shanty at the base of the cliff, you've gone too far.

GPS: 38.47033, -109.22393

content.description: Mixed gear and bolts line up a shallow right-facing dihedral that continues up the face.
A bouldery start that tempts you to climb off course but punishes you if you do.  Follow the bolt line religiously for a long, classic climb up and out of the shade of the trees.
content.protection: 12 bolts and Rap hangers (along with a few pitons)
content.location:
Starts just to the right of the Shanty and climbs past a small bush, veering to the left as you climb higher and roughly following a rain runnel.

GPS: 38.47033, -109.22393

content.description: Just to the left of Cockblocker, Roofus climbs an arete to a slabbier face, then up and over the roof (above and to the left of Cockblocker's anchors).
A beautiful, meandering face climb up an unlikely-looking face with hidden holds that make it possible.
content.location:
Around the corner from the arch-like feature and in a hidden cove on the right-side wall.

GPS: 38.470307, -109.274425

content.description: A thin start on a mild slab face climbs up to the left side of an arch-like feature and onto the shelf above it.  Shares anchors with "Is This Love?".
content.location: Under an arch-like feature and up the left side.

content.description: A fine hands crack up to a ledge partway up.  If you want to finish the climb, pull out your draws and finish a 5.12 sport arete to the true top of the wall.
content.location:
Left face of the pretty cove up the left crack to an obvious ledge near the top.

GPS: 38.470293, -109.274543

content.description: Starts under an Arch-like feature on the right side in a strange chimney.  A cruxy exit from the chimney to the face leads out and eventually onto a large shelf.  Shares anchor with "No More Trouble".
content.location: Under and Arch like feature in the chimney on the right.

content.description: An unbelievable dihedral climb with lots of smearing, palming, mantelling, and flexibility needed.  Think you can climb 5.9?  Think again!  Ends in a beautiful hands crack.
content.location:
This climb is the left dihedral in a pretty cove in the rock face.  It starts up a ramping slab just to the right of the crack.

GPS: 38.470344, -109.274536

content.description: Steep start that finished up an arete.
Starts just to the right of a detached pillar.  Occasionally tricky climbing.
content.location: Starts just to the right of a detached pillar and climbs a featured face.

content.description: Two-toned rock up to the rim in a beautiful little cove.
content.location:
On the right side of a pretty cove across from a beautiful sheer wall split by two cracks.

GPS: 38.470307, -109.274425

content.description: This amazing climb utilizes dual opposing gastons with great feet up to a hidden anchor on the back side a balanced boulder.
content.location:
This route climbs directly beneath a large balanced block to a 2-bolt anchor.

GPS: 38.470437, -109.275484

content.description: Climbs directly above the Shanty to share the chains of Screwface.
